<head>
<title>David A. Keene Bio -- ACU</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<img alt="Picture of David Keene" src="keene.gif"><br>
<h3>David A. Keene<br>
1007 Cameron Street<br>
Alexandria, VA 22314</h3></center>
<hr>
<p>
David A. Keene, 50, is a Senior Associate with Linton, Mields, Reisler &amp; Cottone, Inc., a governmental affairs and legislative relations firm based in Washington, D.C. and editor of <EM><U>The Keene Report</U></EM>, a political newsletter.  He is a graduate of the University of Wisconsin and Wisconsin Law School.

Mr. Keene has been a John F. Kennedy fellow at Harvard University and is a former member of the Board of Visitors of the School of Public Policy at Duke University.  Recently, he was a visiting professional scholar at the Freedom Forum First Amendment Center at Vanderbilt University.
<p>
Mr. Keene's political experience is extensive.  He has been involved in Republican presidential politics since 1968.  He worked in the White House during the Nixon Administration as political assistant to Vice President Agnew and on Capitol Hill as Executive Assistant to Senator James L. Buckley.
<P>As Southern Regional Coordinator for Ronald Reagan in 1976 and National Political Director for George Bush in 1980,  Mr. Keene won recognition for his skill as a political organizer and strategist.
<p>
Mr. Keene was a senior political consultant to Republican presidential candidate Robert Dole in 1988 and is an informal advisor this year. He is Chairman of the American Conservative Union (ACU).  Founded in 1964, ACU is the country's leading multi-issue grassroots conservative lobbying and public education organization.  In this capacity Mr. Keene is frequently cited and consulted as an authoritative spokesman on conservative political philosophy, public policy, and contemporary political issues.
<p>
<img alt="Picture of Keene and Gingrich" src="keengin.gif"><p>
