<title>Daily Commentary - January 29, 1997</title>

<body>

<center><h1>Daily Commentary<br>
January 29, 1997</h1></center>

<p><hr width=75% size=3><p>

I'm Gary Bauer for Washington Watch.

<p>

If you're like me, you're tired of watching federal judges impose
their political will.

<p>

Just last week a judge overturned a law keeping pornography from
being sold on military bases.  Recently, an appellate judge ruled it's
unconstitutional for courts to send alcoholics to Alcoholics Anonymous 
because AA acknowledges God.  And another judge threw out 80 pounds 
of heroin and cocaine as evidence in a drug case.

<p>

These cases have two things in common: all of the judges were
appointed by Bill Clinton and all were <I>unanimously</I> approved by 
the Senate. It seems this administration likes activist judges to 
dictate from the bench because their agenda doesn't sell with voters.

<p>

Well my friends, this must stop.  If the Senate won't protect
us from this nonsense, we'll do it ourselves.  That's why FRC has joined a
coalition of over 200 local, state and national organizations dedicated to 
putting an end to judicial tyranny.  We won't long remain a free country 
if we let unelected judges do the work of elected representatives.

<p>

It's time to rule activist judges out of order.  Freedom and
self-government hang in the balance.

<p>

For Family Research Council, this is Gary Bauer with today's
Washington Watch.  For more information about us, call 1-800-225-4008.
That number again:  1-800-225-4008.

<p>

