At an Afrocentric grade school in Milwaukee, children are taught that early Egyptians were black, had wings, and flew around the pyramids, but Europeans came and killed them all. Not that we doubt this for one moment, but we are puzzled that Cheops Le May and the immensely superior Egyptian forces did not simply bomb the invaders back into the Stone Age.
<P>
 <LI>The <I>Washington Post</I> reports that the Administration has been auctioning off overnight accommodations to big Democratic contributors. (For several hundred grand, you too can sleep in the Lincoln bedroom.) Tom Pauken, running for chairman of the Republican National Committee, now refers to the White House as "Motel 1600," which would seem to make Hillary Clinton its Leona Helmsley.

